1
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:11,040
Up off the ground.

2
00:02:11,711 --> 00:02:14,582
That's right, pass it high.
Up off the ground.

3
00:02:16,716 --> 00:02:18,625
Pass it high.

4
00:02:19,135 --> 00:02:22,800
Sal. Take over, will you?

5
00:02:41,992 --> 00:02:45,443
- Hey, I was just looking for you up there.
- I came out by the front.

6
00:02:45,662 --> 00:02:48,070
- Well, you're pretty daring.
- It's perfectly legal.

7
00:02:48,248 --> 00:02:51,582
I just looked it up. A man's allowed
to kiss any girl he's engaged to.

8
00:02:51,752 --> 00:02:53,993
Hey, you're not gonna wear
those pants?

9
00:02:54,171 --> 00:02:56,543
Not pants. They're slacks.
Watch your language.

10
00:02:56,758 --> 00:02:59,427
Look. We got
a pretty delicate deal here.

11
00:02:59,594 --> 00:03:02,002
This game isn't so much pleasure,
more business.

12
00:03:02,180 --> 00:03:04,219
And I don't want anything
to go flooey.

13
00:03:04,390 --> 00:03:07,842
They're pretty conservative people,
these Bemingers, and...

14
00:03:09,896 --> 00:03:14,190
- It's too late now. Come on, let's go.
- No, no, wait. Wait.

15
00:03:24,202 --> 00:03:25,946
Go.

16
00:03:30,375 --> 00:03:33,376
Oh, mister, the things
I've done for this school.

17
00:03:33,545 --> 00:03:36,250
This time it's worth it, honey.
Beminger's good and ripe.

18
00:03:36,423 --> 00:03:37,751
For what?

19
00:03:37,924 --> 00:03:39,882
Biggest donation
I've gotten all year.

20
00:03:40,052 --> 00:03:44,180
- Hooray for our side.
- Your side especially.

21
00:03:44,348 --> 00:03:46,921
He's really serious
about building us that new gym.

22
00:03:47,100 --> 00:03:49,307
How fascinating.

23
00:03:52,481 --> 00:03:56,431
Now, all we've got to do
is the right thing and say it.

24
00:03:56,652 --> 00:03:59,273
- At your service.
- Well, number one, it's he and you...

25
00:03:59,446 --> 00:04:01,818
...against Mrs. Beminger and me.
- Yes, sir.

26
00:04:02,032 --> 00:04:06,030
I could make it look pretty good
and lose, but Mrs. Beminger's a whiz.

27
00:04:06,203 --> 00:04:08,492
- Do or die, that's me.
- Just see that you win.

28
00:04:08,664 --> 00:04:12,448
- Yes, sir. Do my best.
- Let's not blow this.

29
00:04:12,668 --> 00:04:14,910
Yeah, yeah, do my best.

30
00:04:15,129 --> 00:04:17,999
Just watch me.
I'll tell you what to do...

31
00:04:18,174 --> 00:04:20,380
...and then let's hope
you can do it.

32
00:04:20,551 --> 00:04:22,425
- Thanks.
- What?

33
00:04:22,595 --> 00:04:23,923
Nothing.

34
00:04:24,096 --> 00:04:27,679
Well, give us a kiss, honey.
I'm nervous as a cat.

35
00:04:53,460 --> 00:04:55,453
- Good afternoon. Good afternoon.
- Hi.

36
00:04:55,629 --> 00:04:58,583
- How are you, Mrs. Beminger?
- Quite well, thank you.

37
00:04:58,799 --> 00:05:00,341
- Hi.
- Come on, Collier, let's go.

38
00:05:00,509 --> 00:05:03,178
- Eighteen holes is a lot of holes.
- All set.

39
00:05:03,345 --> 00:05:05,836
Say, that's quite a swing
you've got there, Mrs. B.

40
00:05:06,015 --> 00:05:07,557
What do you say, Ma?

41
00:05:07,766 --> 00:05:10,436
I say:

42
00:05:12,438 --> 00:05:14,680
- After you, dear. Okay, Mr. B?
- Yeah.

43
00:05:14,857 --> 00:05:16,481
- Go ahead.
- Got a tee, Coll?

44
00:05:16,650 --> 00:05:17,979
Yeah.

45
00:05:19,695 --> 00:05:22,186
Now, don't let me down, now.
Let's see the good one.

46
00:05:35,628 --> 00:05:38,084
Oh, too bad.

47
00:05:38,297 --> 00:05:41,548
You've got to tense
the gluteal muscles, dear.

48
00:05:41,717 --> 00:05:44,291
If you don't tense
the gluteal muscles...

49
00:05:44,470 --> 00:05:47,922
...why, your whole alignment is off.
- You want me to get you a soapbox?

50
00:05:48,099 --> 00:05:49,510
- Play your cards.
- What?

51
00:05:49,684 --> 00:05:51,059
Tee off.

52
00:05:51,227 --> 00:05:53,552
Thank you, lady.
Thank you very much.

53
00:05:53,730 --> 00:05:56,565
I wouldn't have known what to do
if you hadn't told me.

54
00:05:56,733 --> 00:05:58,275
Thank you.

55
00:06:03,364 --> 00:06:05,855
Oh, tense the gluteal muscles,
did you say?

56
00:06:06,075 --> 00:06:08,034
Yes. That's right.

57
00:06:08,204 --> 00:06:09,318
Tense.

58
00:06:13,334 --> 00:06:16,537
Well, I see what you mean.
Makes all the difference.

59
00:06:16,712 --> 00:06:18,669
- It does.
- All.

60
00:06:20,967 --> 00:06:23,292
Gotta tense. Tense.

61
00:06:57,295 --> 00:07:00,664
Well, for heaven's sake,
I know, don't I?

62
00:07:10,558 --> 00:07:12,183
Beauty.

63
00:07:14,729 --> 00:07:16,852
Take your time, partner.

64
00:07:17,315 --> 00:07:19,438
It's all up to you now, don't forget.

65
00:07:19,609 --> 00:07:21,566
Quiet, do you mind?

66
00:07:46,721 --> 00:07:48,797
My dear, if you would
lean your weight...

67
00:07:48,973 --> 00:07:50,931
...on your right foot, the way I do...

68
00:07:51,101 --> 00:07:53,224
Take into consideration
an endowment...

69
00:07:53,395 --> 00:07:55,102
...that has some permanent value.

70
00:07:55,271 --> 00:07:57,679
What is the concrete thing
that you can point to...

71
00:07:57,857 --> 00:08:00,146
...in the years to come with...?

72
00:08:04,322 --> 00:08:05,864
So all I can say is to...

73
00:08:06,074 --> 00:08:09,158
...consider that every time
you look up at that building...

74
00:08:09,327 --> 00:08:12,531
...you're in a position
to point with pride and...

75
00:08:12,706 --> 00:08:15,161
- that you'll find it is
to develop your reflexes.

76
00:08:15,333 --> 00:08:18,500
Yes, you've got to learn to relax.
To give in.

77
00:08:19,880 --> 00:08:21,707
We can settle this some other time.

78
00:08:24,092 --> 00:08:27,259
- Forty, 60. Come here, boy.
- Yes, sir.

79
00:08:27,429 --> 00:08:29,920
- Split that up.
- How about a nice, tall, cool one?

80
00:08:30,098 --> 00:08:31,758
I'll take mine in the locker room.

81
00:08:31,934 --> 00:08:33,594
See you in 20 minutes
in the lounge.

82
00:08:33,769 --> 00:08:36,342
The one thing he can't stand,
Mr. B, is to lose.

83
00:08:36,522 --> 00:08:39,476
With him, it's not the principle
of the thing, it's the money.

84
00:08:39,650 --> 00:08:42,651
You know, dear, where you go bad
is your coordination.

85
00:08:42,820 --> 00:08:45,311
Now, that is your story, coordination.

86
00:08:45,489 --> 00:08:49,107
This and this and this should
all be parts of the same thing.

87
00:08:49,284 --> 00:08:51,361
If you could possibly lift the needle...

88
00:08:51,537 --> 00:08:54,372
...from that long-playing phonograph
you keep in your face.

89
00:08:54,540 --> 00:08:57,292
Why, the very...

90
00:09:04,675 --> 00:09:07,759
Watch this. Will you excuse me?

91
00:09:24,571 --> 00:09:26,943
You know what you can do
with your gluteal muscle?

92
00:09:27,115 --> 00:09:29,108
Give it away for Christmas.

93
00:09:32,788 --> 00:09:35,872
Say, wait, wait here.
Wait a moment.

94
00:09:38,585 --> 00:09:40,459
Sit down, Mrs. Pemberton,
sit down.

95
00:09:40,629 --> 00:09:42,788
- What will you have to drink?
- Plenty.

96
00:09:42,965 --> 00:09:45,835
- Lemonade?
- Why not?

97
00:09:46,218 --> 00:09:49,172
- Right.
- Strong. Plenty of lemon.

98
00:09:49,346 --> 00:09:52,466
- What do I care?
- All right. Plenty of lemon.

99
00:09:52,641 --> 00:09:55,726
And another thing.
Don't call me Mrs. Pemberton.

100
00:09:55,895 --> 00:09:57,686
- No?
- Pat, that's me.

101
00:09:57,855 --> 00:09:59,764
Okay. I'll call you Pat.

102
00:09:59,940 --> 00:10:03,356
- I want everybody to from now on.
- Why?

103
00:10:03,569 --> 00:10:06,107
Friendless. That's how I feel.

104
00:10:06,322 --> 00:10:10,818
I feel the whole world's against me,
and vice versa.

105
00:10:10,993 --> 00:10:12,950
Did you ever feel that way, Charlie?

106
00:10:13,120 --> 00:10:15,030
Every time I miss a shot.

107
00:10:15,248 --> 00:10:17,121
There you are.

108
00:10:17,875 --> 00:10:19,868
You've been golfing here
for quite a while.

109
00:10:20,044 --> 00:10:21,953
- Quite.
- Then how come I never saw it?

110
00:10:22,130 --> 00:10:23,837
Saw what?

111
00:10:24,006 --> 00:10:25,584
- You're great.
- I must be.

112
00:10:25,758 --> 00:10:27,834
- A natural.
- Fairly seldom.

113
00:10:28,010 --> 00:10:30,466
- What's your handicap?
- My fella.

114
00:10:30,638 --> 00:10:32,963
I mean on the board.

115
00:10:33,725 --> 00:10:35,516
- Six.
- You ought to be two.

116
00:10:35,685 --> 00:10:39,101
- I wish I were a two.
- You know what I'd like to do with you?

117
00:10:39,272 --> 00:10:41,763
Enter you in the Women's National.

118
00:10:42,191 --> 00:10:44,398
- Oh, no.
- Listen, if I don't know a champ...

119
00:10:44,569 --> 00:10:47,060
...when I see one, what good am I?

120
00:10:47,238 --> 00:10:49,278
- Oh, I haven't the time.
- We'll make it.

121
00:10:49,449 --> 00:10:51,109
We'll coach hard the next 15 days.

122
00:10:51,284 --> 00:10:54,321
We'll get out there, you qualify,
you play and you win.

123
00:10:54,497 --> 00:10:56,573
No. I can't play golf.
I can't do anything...

124
00:10:56,749 --> 00:10:59,999
- But what about out there? I saw...
- That was because I got mad. Mad.

125
00:11:00,169 --> 00:11:02,162
- Well, we'll keep you mad.
- No, you see...

126
00:11:02,338 --> 00:11:03,998
...I only play with Collier Weld.

127
00:11:04,173 --> 00:11:06,415
And I can't do anything
when he's watching me.

128
00:11:06,592 --> 00:11:10,044
- Listen, a chance like this...
- Give me Mrs. Beminger's money.

129
00:11:12,515 --> 00:11:14,306
Do you mind, Charlie?

130
00:11:15,435 --> 00:11:17,593
- I thought you wanted to help me.
- I tried to.

131
00:11:17,770 --> 00:11:19,763
To what?
Jam me up with the biggest donor...

132
00:11:19,939 --> 00:11:22,145
- I didn't mean to.
- Pat, I'm trying understand.

133
00:11:22,316 --> 00:11:24,060
How could you,
when I don't myself.

134
00:11:24,235 --> 00:11:26,560
- You don't what?
- Anything. Understand.

135
00:11:26,738 --> 00:11:29,692
Why it is I fall to pieces
whenever you give me that look.

136
00:11:29,866 --> 00:11:31,905
- What look?
- This look.

137
00:11:32,410 --> 00:11:33,904
- That's me?
- Sure.

138
00:11:34,078 --> 00:11:36,569
Makes me feel you don't believe in me
and never will.

139
00:11:36,748 --> 00:11:39,749
- You're just overwrought.
- And you're just overpowering.

140
00:11:39,918 --> 00:11:42,491
- Now, let's not squabble, huh?
- Okay!

141
00:11:42,879 --> 00:11:45,287
I'll see if I can square things
with the Bemingers.

142
00:11:45,465 --> 00:11:47,292
Why try?

143
00:11:48,009 --> 00:11:49,338
Face it, Pat. He's a power.

144
00:11:49,511 --> 00:11:51,966
He's out there screaming
about firing you.

145
00:11:52,597 --> 00:11:54,590
- He couldn't.
- Why not?

146
00:11:54,766 --> 00:11:56,509
- Because I've quit.
- When?

147
00:11:56,685 --> 00:11:59,721
- Right now.
- Oh, no.

148
00:11:59,896 --> 00:12:03,846
- Well, this is no place to talk now.
- Okay, later.

149
00:12:05,861 --> 00:12:09,064
Don't get frazzled, dear.
Don't get frazzled.

150
00:12:14,619 --> 00:12:16,826
Everybody frazzles everybody...

151
00:12:16,997 --> 00:12:19,570
...then they turn around
and tell them, "Don't be."

152
00:12:19,750 --> 00:12:21,292
What?

153
00:12:22,419 --> 00:12:24,577
That true, Charlie?

154
00:12:24,755 --> 00:12:26,249
What's true?

155
00:12:26,423 --> 00:12:28,831
What you think I could do?

156
00:12:30,595 --> 00:12:32,635
Scout's honor.

157
00:12:34,390 --> 00:12:36,182
- All right, then.
- Great.

158
00:12:36,351 --> 00:12:37,893
I'll show her.

159
00:12:38,061 --> 00:12:40,267
- Show who?
- Show myself, that's who.

160
00:12:40,438 --> 00:12:43,558
That's right. Because you know how
to not get yourself frazzled?

161
00:12:43,733 --> 00:12:45,192
Get unfrazzled.

162
00:12:56,204 --> 00:12:58,363
<i>Nearly all of the 60 girls
who have entered...</i>

163
00:12:58,540 --> 00:13:00,283
<i>...have turned in their scorecards.</i>

164
00:13:00,459 --> 00:13:04,159
<i>Let me repeat, ladies and gentlemen,
only the 16 best will be eligible...</i>

165
00:13:04,379 --> 00:13:07,333
<i>...to compete for match play,
which begins tomorrow.</i>

166
00:13:07,507 --> 00:13:10,343
<i>Your attention, ladies and gentlemen,
we have another score.</i>

167
00:13:10,552 --> 00:13:15,629
Mrs. Patricia Pemberton
has just qualified with a sparkling 77.

168
00:13:29,154 --> 00:13:32,239
<i>That, ladies and gentlemen,
leaves one contender still to be...</i>

169
00:13:32,408 --> 00:13:34,946
<i>Yes, here she comes now,
the mighty Babe.</i>

170
00:13:35,160 --> 00:13:39,454
<i>We'll have her score for you
in just a second. Here it is now.</i>

171
00:13:40,040 --> 00:13:42,662
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,
the top score of the day.</i>

172
00:13:42,835 --> 00:13:45,373
<i>Mrs. Babe Didrikson Zaharias
has just qualified...</i>

173
00:13:45,546 --> 00:13:48,037
<i>...with a sensational 73.</i>

174
00:13:48,215 --> 00:13:49,923
Now, fellas, here's the rundown.

175
00:13:50,092 --> 00:13:52,583
From left to right,
Beverly Hanson, Babe Zaharias...

176
00:13:52,762 --> 00:13:55,881
...Helen Dettweiler,
Betty Hicks, Mary Lorgan...

177
00:13:56,057 --> 00:13:58,630
...Harriet Salter
and Mrs. Patricia Pemberton.

178
00:15:02,083 --> 00:15:05,037
- Don't be scared, lady.
- What is this, anyway?

179
00:15:05,253 --> 00:15:07,744
Sit down. Come over here
and sit down. Take it easy.

180
00:15:07,964 --> 00:15:11,167
I never like to see an athlete
wear hisself out. Or herself.

181
00:15:11,342 --> 00:15:14,711
- Lf this is a holdup or a robbery...
- We didn't come to be insulted.

182
00:15:14,887 --> 00:15:16,216
- Take it easy.
- Tell her.

183
00:15:16,389 --> 00:15:17,848
- Identify ourselves.
- Sit down.

184
00:15:18,016 --> 00:15:19,842
You've been on your feet
the whole day.

185
00:15:20,018 --> 00:15:22,057
Why don't you sit down
and take it easy.

186
00:15:23,563 --> 00:15:27,062
Mrs. Pemberton, I'd like to
introduce myself. Mike Conovan.

187
00:15:27,233 --> 00:15:29,356
And my associate, Barney Grau.

188
00:15:29,527 --> 00:15:31,187
- Pleasure.
- Take a chair, Barney.

189
00:15:31,362 --> 00:15:32,691
Thank you.

190
00:15:33,406 --> 00:15:37,404
I have been watching you
like eagle eye the last couple of days.

191
00:15:37,577 --> 00:15:42,121
And I'm here to tell you, you are
one beautiful thing to watch. In action.

192
00:15:42,291 --> 00:15:45,126
I've been in this sports racket
as long as I can remember...

193
00:15:45,336 --> 00:15:48,337
...and I'm here to say,
you are what I call, no doubt, fast.

194
00:15:48,506 --> 00:15:49,834
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

195
00:15:50,007 --> 00:15:52,083
Let me ask you
a plain statement of fact.

196
00:15:52,260 --> 00:15:53,718
You figure to win this?

197
00:15:53,886 --> 00:15:55,962
- So does everybody.
- Never mind everybody.

198
00:15:56,139 --> 00:15:58,843
Let's concentrate on you
for an instance.

199
00:15:59,016 --> 00:16:01,554
- Yes or no?
- Yes.

200
00:16:01,853 --> 00:16:05,802
Tell me, off the record,
what's your pitch?

201
00:16:05,982 --> 00:16:08,817
- Well, I don't quite understand what...
- What is it with you?

202
00:16:08,985 --> 00:16:11,986
Is it business, pleasure?
You wanna get a picture in the paper?

203
00:16:12,155 --> 00:16:14,990
- I'm coming to that. I think...
- I really don't know what...

204
00:16:15,158 --> 00:16:18,361
Figure it out, honey.
You're a cinch to win this, you know.

205
00:16:18,536 --> 00:16:20,612
You can't miss copping
this thing in a walk.

206
00:16:20,788 --> 00:16:23,326
- Without someone dismantles you.
- Oh, I don't know.

207
00:16:23,500 --> 00:16:25,991
You're not supposed to know.
You're supposed to play.

208
00:16:26,169 --> 00:16:28,541
I'm supposed to know, and I do.

209
00:16:29,255 --> 00:16:30,666
Tell me...

210
00:16:30,882 --> 00:16:33,124
How smart are you, anyway?

211
00:16:33,301 --> 00:16:35,875
Very, in some things.

212
00:16:36,054 --> 00:16:38,426
How's about money?
What kind of a thing is that?

213
00:16:38,598 --> 00:16:43,474
- Not very.
- Oh, that's too bad. That's too bad.

214
00:16:43,645 --> 00:16:46,646
Because I got a way for you
to stash away a roll, surprise you.

215
00:16:46,815 --> 00:16:48,642
I'd like that.

216
00:16:49,317 --> 00:16:50,646
You would?

217
00:16:51,445 --> 00:16:53,900
How would you like
to come in second?

218
00:16:56,992 --> 00:16:59,827
- I wouldn't.
- A square, like I figured.

219
00:16:59,995 --> 00:17:02,568
That's too bad. That's too bad.

220
00:17:02,748 --> 00:17:05,239
You come in second,
you could do very good in money.

221
00:17:05,417 --> 00:17:08,252
Come in first, you get a cup.
It's too big to drink out of.

222
00:17:08,420 --> 00:17:11,456
- I think you'd better get out.
- Mention a number. Think it over.

223
00:17:11,632 --> 00:17:13,042
Here, this is me.

224
00:17:13,217 --> 00:17:15,505
In New York, strictly legitimate
and well known.

225
00:17:15,678 --> 00:17:18,086
I own and operate Davie Hucko.

226
00:17:18,598 --> 00:17:21,718
- Davie Hucko, mean anything?
- No.

227
00:17:25,063 --> 00:17:27,471
- No.
- Heavyweight champion of the world...

228
00:17:27,649 --> 00:17:30,140
...in a couple of years.
Now to get back to you.

229
00:17:30,318 --> 00:17:32,275
The only thing you gotta do
is to lose...

230
00:17:32,445 --> 00:17:35,363
...and our only problem is gonna be
to find bushel baskets...

231
00:17:35,532 --> 00:17:37,192
...to carry the stuff away.

232
00:17:37,492 --> 00:17:38,821
- Yes?
- Room service.

233
00:17:38,994 --> 00:17:40,322
Just a minute.

