00:38:34,153 --> 00:38:36,609
Oh, no, no. Just hit a couple.

464
00:39:32,547 --> 00:39:35,797
- Got to be notary public, don't it?
- Take care of that, don't worry.

465
00:39:35,967 --> 00:39:37,627
We ought to have a glass for luck.

466
00:39:37,802 --> 00:39:39,462
What do you mean, a glass for luck?

467
00:39:39,679 --> 00:39:41,885
What am I, some kind
of an acey-deucey gambler?

468
00:39:42,056 --> 00:39:45,390
Us two bumping into each other,
that's all the luck any man deserves.

469
00:39:45,560 --> 00:39:48,181
From now on, it's hard work
and promotion and so forth.

470
00:39:48,354 --> 00:39:50,892
- And promotion.
- Okay, I'll get these back to you.

471
00:39:51,065 --> 00:39:52,809
- And yours too, miss.
- Thank you.

472
00:39:53,026 --> 00:39:56,062
- So let's go.
- I'd like a martini, please. Very, very dry.

473
00:39:56,237 --> 00:39:58,230
- Very, very nothing. Cancel that.
- What?

474
00:39:58,406 --> 00:39:59,735
- Beer, beer.
- Beer, beer.

475
00:39:59,949 --> 00:40:02,322
- Corned beef, Swiss on rye.
- Corned beef.

476
00:40:02,494 --> 00:40:04,036
- I'll have beef stew.
- Same.

477
00:40:04,245 --> 00:40:06,783
- And for the lady?
- Oh, a small steak, rare.

478
00:40:06,956 --> 00:40:08,285
- Medium.
- Rare, rare, rare...

479
00:40:08,458 --> 00:40:10,285
...and a baked potato
and some spinach.

480
00:40:10,460 --> 00:40:12,251
- Coffee?
- Yeah, yeah, coffee.

481
00:40:12,420 --> 00:40:14,128
- Yes, please, large.
- No, no, milk.

482
00:40:14,297 --> 00:40:17,215
- Please, will you, I'm a busy man.
- Two coffees and one milk.

483
00:40:17,384 --> 00:40:20,088
Everybody keeps having to change
one another's minds.

484
00:40:20,262 --> 00:40:23,547
Took a whole half an hour for one...
Could be here for...

485
00:40:23,723 --> 00:40:25,716
- What's the matter?
- Who's talking to you?

486
00:40:25,892 --> 00:40:28,430
- Who, then?
- Myself. Mind if I talk to myself?

487
00:40:29,688 --> 00:40:31,312
I'd like a martini, please.

488
00:40:31,481 --> 00:40:34,518
Look, girlie, do me a favor,
don't be hard to handle, will you?

489
00:40:34,693 --> 00:40:36,602
It's gonna be hard enough
if you're easy.

490
00:40:36,778 --> 00:40:38,937
- I don't see what right...
- Read your contract.

491
00:40:39,114 --> 00:40:41,237
- What? Just silly.
- Training clause.

492
00:40:41,408 --> 00:40:44,077
Well, that's not for you
to decide, you know.

493
00:40:44,286 --> 00:40:48,236
- I have to watch your shape.
- There's nothing wrong with my...

494
00:40:48,540 --> 00:40:52,538
- What shape are you talking about?
- What shape are you talking about?

495
00:40:52,711 --> 00:40:55,083
I'm in perfect condition,
if that's what you mean.

496
00:40:55,255 --> 00:40:56,833
Good. Let's keep you that way.

497
00:40:57,007 --> 00:40:59,130
- We got a long way to go.
- I must say.

498
00:40:59,301 --> 00:41:02,338
Oh, now, now.
Don't race your motor.

499
00:41:09,437 --> 00:41:11,229
- What is this?
- What?

500
00:41:11,398 --> 00:41:12,892
What, you trying to needle me?

501
00:41:13,066 --> 00:41:15,853
- I'm sorry, I don't...
- There's a sign, "No smoking."

502
00:41:16,027 --> 00:41:18,565
- Where?
- I just put it up inside your head.

503
00:41:18,738 --> 00:41:21,312
- See, the point of...
- What?

504
00:41:22,576 --> 00:41:25,612
What's to prevent me smoking
when you're not around?

505
00:41:25,829 --> 00:41:27,869
When am I not around?

506
00:41:28,040 --> 00:41:32,037
Well, you don't expect
to be watching me every minute...

507
00:41:33,086 --> 00:41:36,751
...out of every 24 hours...

508
00:41:36,924 --> 00:41:39,497
...out of every day, do you?

509
00:41:39,927 --> 00:41:42,797
- Lf I have to, sure.
- Not sure I'll like that.

510
00:41:42,971 --> 00:41:44,631
Not asking you to like it.

511
00:41:44,807 --> 00:41:48,176
But you'll see, pretty soon,
I'll trust you, because you'll trust me.

512
00:41:48,352 --> 00:41:51,555
What's good for you is good for me.
And you for me. We're the same.

513
00:41:51,730 --> 00:41:54,517
We're equal.
We're partners, see? 5-0-5-0.

514
00:41:54,733 --> 00:41:56,642
You gotta realize
your body's important.

515
00:41:56,819 --> 00:41:58,396
And it's important to me too.

516
00:41:58,612 --> 00:42:01,732
I ain't letting you throw
no martinis down there, or no smoke.

517
00:42:01,949 --> 00:42:04,238
No more than I let them down
Little Nell.

518
00:42:04,410 --> 00:42:07,197
- Who's that?
- Oh, that's my horse.

519
00:42:10,541 --> 00:42:12,165
She may win Saturday.

520
00:42:12,334 --> 00:42:14,126
Hold the thought.

521
00:42:14,295 --> 00:42:18,506
And another thing, no late hours.
And of course men are out.

522
00:42:18,674 --> 00:42:21,675
In any manner, shape or form.

523
00:42:21,886 --> 00:42:23,594
You're in training.

524
00:42:23,804 --> 00:42:25,762
Go on, now. Eat your food.
Nice and slow.

525
00:42:25,932 --> 00:42:27,889
Kind of, you know, relaxed inside.

526
00:42:29,393 --> 00:42:31,552
Don't forget to throw me over
your shoulder...

527
00:42:31,729 --> 00:42:34,516
...and burp me after lunch.
- I will if you need it.

528
00:42:37,276 --> 00:42:38,605
I'm so glad...

529
00:42:38,778 --> 00:42:42,563
...you plan to look after me
as well as you do your horse.

530
00:42:43,117 --> 00:42:45,524
You wanna joke? Joke.

531
00:42:46,537 --> 00:42:47,865
But I'll tell you something.

532
00:42:48,038 --> 00:42:50,446
Someday you'll realize something,
and that is this:

533
00:42:50,624 --> 00:42:54,076
We all gotta work together, see?
We all gotta cooperate.

534
00:42:54,295 --> 00:42:56,252
Everybody's sitting around the place.

535
00:42:56,463 --> 00:42:58,705
Everybody's sitting around the world.

536
00:42:58,883 --> 00:43:02,049
And everybody's brain
has got something cooking inside, see?

537
00:43:03,220 --> 00:43:05,758
Well, nobody's got
a better dream than me.

538
00:43:05,931 --> 00:43:08,387
- Believe me, I stand them off.
- What is it?

539
00:43:08,559 --> 00:43:11,097
I can see myself with greats.

540
00:43:11,604 --> 00:43:16,230
I can wind up with the top man,
the top horse and the top woman.

541
00:43:56,441 --> 00:43:59,442
<i>Advantage,
Mrs. Pemberton and Mr. Parker.</i>

542
00:44:23,052 --> 00:44:25,377
<i>Game to Mrs. Pemberton
and Mr. Parker.</i>

543
00:44:25,555 --> 00:44:28,591
<i>They lead five games to three
in the first set.</i>

544
00:44:50,205 --> 00:44:51,865
- That's enough. You'd better quit.
- Not yet.

545
00:44:52,040 --> 00:44:55,041
Don't wanna get all tired out.
You got a long day.

546
00:44:55,251 --> 00:44:57,956
- Long and hard.
- Why hard?

547
00:44:58,171 --> 00:45:00,413
Oh, I don't know.

548
00:45:01,216 --> 00:45:04,252
This place and
all the different people turning up.

549
00:45:04,427 --> 00:45:08,128
- You know, ones I know.
- Well, why? I don't dig that.

550
00:45:08,306 --> 00:45:12,636
I should think you'd be great.
Your hometown. Did that flower...?

551
00:45:12,811 --> 00:45:15,563
Maybe I would, if it weren't for...

552
00:45:27,828 --> 00:45:30,402
Come on, now.
You'd better quit. You're puffing again.

553
00:45:30,581 --> 00:45:33,915
Barney say that more than 100
of my Pacific Tech girls are out there?

554
00:45:34,085 --> 00:45:36,291
No, no. They got a friend for me?

555
00:45:36,462 --> 00:45:38,205
- Announcing.
- That's it. That's it.

556
00:45:38,381 --> 00:45:40,504
Now, will you please remember,
start slow.

557
00:45:40,675 --> 00:45:42,584
Don't show them
all your stuff at once.

558
00:45:42,760 --> 00:45:46,805
Remember, you're the best.
Even if you don't think so, I do.

559
00:45:46,973 --> 00:45:49,214
- Just play your regular game, you know?
- Yeah.

560
00:45:49,392 --> 00:45:52,179
It's beautiful. Just like you.

561
00:45:54,690 --> 00:45:56,932
You know what I'm going to do?
For luck?

562
00:45:57,109 --> 00:46:00,644
- No.
- Give you a great big kiss.

563
00:46:01,739 --> 00:46:04,490
If you don't start slow, by the 15th or
16th game...

564
00:46:04,825 --> 00:46:06,070
...you're gonna start to press.

565
00:46:06,243 --> 00:46:08,283
We gotta remember,
the money dates are coming up.

566
00:46:08,454 --> 00:46:10,696
The big money dates.

567
00:46:20,174 --> 00:46:21,798
Ladies and gentlemen...

568
00:46:21,967 --> 00:46:25,336
...the next match will be between
Pat Pemberton of Oakland...

569
00:46:25,513 --> 00:46:27,968
...and Gussie Moran
of Santa Monica, California.

570
00:46:28,349 --> 00:46:30,223
- Where's he sitting?
- Who's sitting?

571
00:46:30,393 --> 00:46:32,136
- Collier.
- Over here. X4.

572
00:46:32,311 --> 00:46:35,146
- Introducing Gorgeous Gussie.
- Are you sure?

573
00:46:35,314 --> 00:46:36,345
Am I sure?

574
00:46:36,524 --> 00:46:39,441
- Paid for it myself. He's on the cuffola.
- Thanks.

575
00:46:39,610 --> 00:46:41,686
I'd have paid better
if he'd stayed home.

576
00:46:41,863 --> 00:46:47,652
And her opponent,
California's own Pat Pemberton.

577
00:46:58,963 --> 00:47:00,541
Drop it.

578
00:47:01,925 --> 00:47:04,250
- Rough it is. I'll start over there.
- I'll serve.

579
00:47:04,427 --> 00:47:06,005
Wait, shake hands.

580
00:47:06,179 --> 00:47:08,752
- That's it. Thanks a lot.
- Where's the smile, Pat?

581
00:47:08,932 --> 00:47:11,601
- That's fine. That's it, girls.
- Thank you.

582
00:47:38,171 --> 00:47:40,744
This is the feature event
of the afternoon...

583
00:47:40,923 --> 00:47:43,414
...climaxing a cross-country tour.

584
00:47:43,593 --> 00:47:46,000
As of today, Mrs. Pemberton
and Miss Moran...

585
00:47:46,179 --> 00:47:48,966
...are tied with 22 matches apiece.

586
00:47:49,140 --> 00:47:53,054
This match will be
the best two out of three sets.

587
00:47:55,563 --> 00:47:57,556
Linesmen ready.

588
00:47:57,732 --> 00:47:59,523
Players ready.

589
00:48:00,276 --> 00:48:01,818
Mrs. Pemberton will serve first.

590
00:48:02,946 --> 00:48:04,654
Play.

591
00:48:21,381 --> 00:48:23,374
Fifteen, Mrs. Pemberton.

592
00:48:40,067 --> 00:48:41,976
Thirty-love.

593
00:49:09,180 --> 00:49:11,387
Forty-love.

594
00:49:42,881 --> 00:49:44,541
Game to Mrs. Pemberton.

595
00:49:44,716 --> 00:49:47,587
She leads one game to love
in the first set.

596
00:49:48,554 --> 00:49:51,923
Mrs. Pemberton won the first set,
six games to three.

597
00:49:52,141 --> 00:49:56,008
She now leads three games to two
in the second set.

598
00:50:22,797 --> 00:50:25,466
Fifteen, Mrs. Pemberton.

599
00:50:56,123 --> 00:50:59,622
Double fault. Fifteen-all.

600
00:51:21,315 --> 00:51:23,723
Fifteen-30.

601
00:51:36,038 --> 00:51:39,704
- Double fault, 15-40.
- She plays pretty good at times.

602
00:51:39,876 --> 00:51:42,746
She just gets that way
every once in a while.

603
00:52:10,031 --> 00:52:12,522
Game, Miss Moran.

604
00:52:13,410 --> 00:52:15,154
Where's my racket?

605
00:53:35,827 --> 00:53:39,161
- There she is.
- There she is, come on.

606
00:53:39,331 --> 00:53:41,205
That's a girl.

607
00:53:41,375 --> 00:53:42,703
All right.

608
00:53:42,876 --> 00:53:44,786
I just couldn't make anything behave.

609
00:53:44,962 --> 00:53:48,247
Oh, that happens.
You know, a little slump. A dip.

610
00:53:48,424 --> 00:53:50,797
- A couple of weeks' rest.
- No, I'm okay.

611
00:53:50,969 --> 00:53:53,507
We're going over to Elkwood Acres
over in New Jersey.

612
00:53:53,680 --> 00:53:55,388
- Wonderful place.
- No, I'm all right.

613
00:53:55,557 --> 00:53:59,389
You mean more to me than all them
bucks. I'm gonna take care of you good.

614
00:53:59,561 --> 00:54:02,930
Who's that? Tell them to go away.

615
00:54:03,106 --> 00:54:06,060
- Oh, you poor darling.
- Oh, hello, Coll.

616
00:54:06,234 --> 00:54:08,690
I'm all right.
Wasn't that a mess, though?

617
00:54:08,862 --> 00:54:12,361
- Oh, this is Mr. Conovan. Mr. Weld.
- Hello.

618
00:54:12,532 --> 00:54:14,406
How do you do?
I'm taking you home, Pat.

619
00:54:14,576 --> 00:54:17,530
- Now, get your things together.
- No. No, I'm all right here.

620
00:54:17,704 --> 00:54:19,033
If you'll excuse us, please?

621
00:54:19,206 --> 00:54:20,783
If it's about going somewhere...

622
00:54:20,958 --> 00:54:23,793
...I'd like to stick around.
I'd like to kind of be on it.

623
00:54:23,961 --> 00:54:26,997
- I'm sorry. We can't oblige.
- Well, I have a contract, you know.

624
00:54:27,172 --> 00:54:30,007
- I'll send you a copy of it. It says plain.
- Look, friend.

625
00:54:30,175 --> 00:54:32,845
You've been responsible
for wrecking this girl's health.

626
00:54:33,011 --> 00:54:36,427
- I'm not gonna let her stay around.
- Let's not raise your voice, now.

627
00:54:36,598 --> 00:54:39,136
You don't intimidate me.
I've never even heard of you.

628
00:54:39,309 --> 00:54:42,725
No, but I've heard of you.
Joe Jinx, that's you.

629
00:54:42,896 --> 00:54:47,190
Except when you're around, we got
a very valuable piece of property here.

630
00:54:47,359 --> 00:54:50,111
And, you know, I ain't
the only one concerned, you know.

631
00:54:50,279 --> 00:54:52,817
I own the biggest piece
of this kid, 51 percent.

632
00:54:52,990 --> 00:54:57,451
But there are other guys, you know,
that are in too, that own small pieces.

633
00:54:57,620 --> 00:55:01,320
And with her potential, I don't think
they'd like to see it all pulled...

634
00:55:01,499 --> 00:55:03,159
...right out from under them.

635
00:55:03,334 --> 00:55:07,332
Now, I am in no position
to mention their names by name...

636
00:55:07,505 --> 00:55:09,213
...but I can tell you this:

637
00:55:09,382 --> 00:55:11,837
They are the kind of types
that have been known...

638
00:55:12,009 --> 00:55:14,500
...to act very hotheaded
in their day and age.

639
00:55:14,679 --> 00:55:18,012
Look, Conovan, you may think
that you own 51 percent of her...

640
00:55:18,182 --> 00:55:20,305
...but you'll find out
that I own all of her.

641
00:55:20,476 --> 00:55:22,552
No, you don't.
Get away from me, all of you.

642
00:55:22,728 --> 00:55:25,599
Nobody owns anything
of anybody except myself.

643
00:55:25,773 --> 00:55:27,814
Go away, both of you.

644
00:55:27,985 --> 00:55:29,609
Leave me alone.

645
00:55:29,778 --> 00:55:31,320
Leave me alone.

646
00:55:31,488 --> 00:55:33,315
- Just go away.
- Well, I'll...

647
00:55:33,490 --> 00:55:36,741
- I'll be back.
- Go away. Go away.

648
00:55:44,251 --> 00:55:47,038
Hey, what is this?
What's happened here?

649
00:55:47,213 --> 00:55:49,170
What's happened?

650
00:55:56,305 --> 00:56:01,097
Hey. Hey, hey, slow down.

651
00:56:03,271 --> 00:56:05,940
- How you holding?
- Okay.

652
00:56:06,107 --> 00:56:09,690
- Feet heavy?
- Mine's heavy, Mike.

653
00:56:09,861 --> 00:56:13,728
Well, yours are supposed to be heavy.
You're a heavyweight, ain't you?

654
00:56:14,615 --> 00:56:16,691
Yeah, that's right.

655
00:56:16,868 --> 00:56:20,533
Like I told you.
Don't feel like running, slow down.

656
00:56:20,705 --> 00:56:22,994
You're supposed to feel like it.

657
00:56:23,166 --> 00:56:25,205
That shows you're in condition.

658
00:56:25,835 --> 00:56:28,456
People do like they feel,
they go on sometimes...

659
00:56:28,630 --> 00:56:30,421
...practically forever, some of them.

660
00:56:30,590 --> 00:56:34,967
Guess you'll go on practically forever
if you stay on that bike.

661
00:56:35,762 --> 00:56:38,300
You're the best
because you feel right.

662
00:56:38,515 --> 00:56:42,215
I tell you, last week I was worried.
I'd just like to mention.

663
00:56:42,519 --> 00:56:44,428
And it was my fault, too.
I'm sorry.

664
00:56:44,604 --> 00:56:48,103
- Nothing to do with you.
- Yeah, pushed you too hard, too fast.

665
00:56:48,274 --> 00:56:50,647
I know what it was.

666
00:56:51,152 --> 00:56:53,441
- Can't you tell me?
- Too personal.

667
00:56:53,613 --> 00:56:55,736
Hey.

668
00:56:57,701 --> 00:56:59,278
Hey.

669
00:56:59,452 --> 00:57:02,704
There should be nothing too personal
between the two of you and me.

670
00:57:02,874 --> 00:57:04,416
It was Collier.

671
00:57:04,584 --> 00:57:06,872
I never can do anything
when he's watching me.

672
00:57:07,044 --> 00:57:09,084
It's always been that way.

673
00:57:09,255 --> 00:57:12,291
- Why?
- Love with him, I guess.

674
00:57:12,467 --> 00:57:15,717
- Oh, like me with lobster.
- What?

675
00:57:15,887 --> 00:57:17,381
Lobster.

676
00:57:17,555 --> 00:57:19,014
The one thing I'm nuts about.

677
00:57:19,182 --> 00:57:21,056
The one thing
that don't agree with me.

678
00:57:21,225 --> 00:57:23,432
- Like you and him.
- Not exactly.

679
00:57:23,603 --> 00:57:24,931
Why?

680
00:57:25,104 --> 00:57:28,853
Well, you see,
this is a question of getting married.

681
00:57:29,025 --> 00:57:32,109
You've never been married
to a lobster.

682
00:57:33,613 --> 00:57:35,736
That's what you think.

683
00:57:41,329 --> 00:57:42,658
- Hey, knock it off!
- Lights.

684
00:57:42,831 --> 00:57:44,159
What do you think is this?

685
00:57:44,332 --> 00:57:46,704
- Hold it, will you?
- It's Mike. Hurry up.

686
00:57:51,298 --> 00:57:53,255
- What is this?
- Just finishing, Mike.

687
00:57:53,425 --> 00:57:55,417
- Do you know what time it is?
- In a minute.

688
00:57:55,594 --> 00:58:01,964
- Ten after 9.
- Oh, gee, now we'll never know.

689
00:58:02,142 --> 00:58:04,680
I want you in bed,
asleep in five minutes, you get it?

690
00:58:04,853 --> 00:58:06,929
No comic books.
Go right to sleep, get that?

691
00:58:07,105 --> 00:58:08,516
Right to sleep, yeah, Mike.

692
00:58:08,690 --> 00:58:11,264
- I'll give it to you for letting him.
- I lost my head.

693
00:58:11,443 --> 00:58:13,768
In your position,
you shouldn't get so engrossed.

694
00:58:13,946 --> 00:58:15,606
Let's go.

695
00:58:21,912 --> 00:58:24,284
I was thinking about all that stuff
on the road.

696
00:58:24,456 --> 00:58:25,785
- Me too.
- Yeah.

697
00:58:25,958 --> 00:58:29,493
Funny how things come out like that.
Yeah, sure is.

698
00:58:29,670 --> 00:58:32,243
- Good night.
- Well, I'll go in with you.

699
00:58:32,423 --> 00:58:34,830
- Yeah? Why?
- Some things I wanna go over with you.

700
00:58:35,009 --> 00:58:36,836
Well, couldn't they wait?

701
00:58:37,012 --> 00:58:40,013
Well, maybe they could,
but I don't know if I could.

702
00:58:40,265 --> 00:58:44,808
- The only thing is my manager.
- Your manager?

703
00:58:44,978 --> 00:58:48,477
He's a little strict, and to tell you
the truth, I'm a bit scared of him.

704
00:58:48,648 --> 00:58:50,143
You are?

705
00:58:50,317 --> 00:58:52,986
I don't drink.
That's on account of him.

706
00:58:53,153 --> 00:58:54,481
Or smoke. That's him too.

707
00:58:54,654 --> 00:58:57,691
- The thing he's strictest about is men.
- Men, huh?

708
00:58:57,866 --> 00:59:02,243
Yeah, you know, dates and late hours
and emotional involvements.

709
00:59:02,412 --> 00:59:03,871
- And...
- He's got a point there.

710
00:59:04,039 --> 00:59:07,373
In fact, he doesn't even want me
to have anything to do with my fella.

711
00:59:07,543 --> 00:59:08,918
- No.
- No.

712
00:59:09,086 --> 00:59:12,040
You make him sound
like an awful gumboil.

713
00:59:12,214 --> 00:59:15,215
Oh, I don't know.
He's not so bad, really.

714
00:59:15,384 --> 00:59:18,136
I think I'm just an animal to him,
like Little Nell.

715
00:59:18,303 --> 00:59:19,762
- Is that what you think?
- Yeah.

716
00:59:19,930 --> 00:59:22,599
You sound like a gumboil yourself.

717
00:59:23,392 --> 00:59:25,883
- Good night.
- Good night.

718
01:00:15,446 --> 01:00:18,482
Come here, little girl.
Come here.

719
01:00:50,982 --> 01:00:53,520
If you only were, honey.

720
01:01:02,493 --> 01:01:04,403
Hey, Barn.

721
01:01:04,579 --> 01:01:07,248
Hey, where'd you drop from?

722
01:01:07,415 --> 01:01:09,573
- Hello, Barn.
- Something happen?

723
01:01:09,751 --> 01:01:11,992
- The bout off?
- No, on.

724
01:01:12,170 --> 01:01:14,376
- So far.
- Then what?

725
01:01:14,547 --> 01:01:17,714
I have to talk to him,
Mike, is all I know.

726
01:01:17,884 --> 01:01:22,760
- So why couldn't you use the phone?
- Because people hang up.

727
01:01:22,931 --> 01:01:25,172
- Where is he?
- Inside.

728
01:01:25,350 --> 01:01:26,809
With her.

729
01:01:26,976 --> 01:01:29,550
You go to the head of the class.

730
01:01:32,857 --> 01:01:35,183
- What are they doing?
- He's examining her.

731
01:01:35,360 --> 01:01:37,187
- Why?
- Why do you think?

732
01:01:37,362 --> 01:01:39,022
He wants to see into her condition.

733
01:01:39,197 --> 01:01:41,984
Why don't he examine me?
Ain't I fighting Friday?

734
01:01:42,158 --> 01:01:44,068
Because you he's not worried about.

735
01:01:44,244 --> 01:01:47,161
- He's worried about her.
- He's worried about her condition.

736
01:01:47,330 --> 01:01:50,950
He'd like to see her make out
next week down at that pro match.

737
01:01:51,961 --> 01:01:53,835
Why don't he examine
into my condition?

738
01:01:54,005 --> 01:01:55,665
Ain't I fighting Friday?

739
01:01:55,840 --> 01:02:00,668
Davie, talking to you sometime is like
taking a ride on a merry-go-round.

740
01:02:00,845 --> 01:02:03,336
The last time I was
on a merry-go-round, I threw up.

741
01:02:03,514 --> 01:02:06,302
- That's good.
- I went on that up-and-down one.

742
01:02:06,476 --> 01:02:08,350
- That's what did it.
- Going up and down?

743
01:02:08,519 --> 01:02:10,559
Everybody goes up and down.

744
01:02:12,357 --> 01:02:14,065
Why don't he examine me?

745
01:02:14,234 --> 01:02:15,562
Quit bugging me, will you?

746
01:02:15,735 --> 01:02:19,318
I mentioned about my stitch,
but he don't care.

747
01:02:19,489 --> 01:02:22,988
Because I've been knocked out
the last four times, he's lost faith in me.

748
01:02:23,159 --> 01:02:26,659
- Funny guy.
- I don't think it's his fault.

749
01:02:26,830 --> 01:02:29,118
I think it's her fault.

750
01:02:29,374 --> 01:02:31,865
Boy, I'd like to take a poke at her.

751
01:02:32,043 --> 01:02:35,459
What are you looking for,
five straight knockouts?

752
01:02:40,051 --> 01:02:41,795
Fifty hops.

753
01:02:42,888 --> 01:02:44,512
Better turn out you're okay.

754
01:02:44,681 --> 01:02:46,888
Otherwise we skip
the whole tournament.

755
01:02:47,059 --> 01:02:49,894
- Feel fine.
- I'll let you know soon how you feel.

756
01:02:50,062 --> 01:02:53,810
- I'd feel even better if I didn't do this.
- Quiet.

757
01:03:00,197 --> 01:03:02,984
Forty-eight, 49, 50.

758
01:03:05,244 --> 01:03:06,786
- Still going?
- What?

759
01:03:06,954 --> 01:03:10,157
I say, is it still going?

760
01:03:12,960 --> 01:03:15,415
- All right, lay down.
- Gladly. On my back or what?

761
01:03:15,587 --> 01:03:17,212
On your what.

762
01:03:20,676 --> 01:03:22,799
If I hurt you, just yell out.

763
01:03:25,223 --> 01:03:28,723
- You got a knot in there.
- Can work it out.

764
01:03:32,272 --> 01:03:33,897
Hello. Hello. Hello.

765
01:03:34,065 --> 01:03:35,560
Who?

766
01:03:35,942 --> 01:03:37,485
What?

767
01:03:37,652 --> 01:03:39,444
Long distance?

768
01:03:39,613 --> 01:03:43,231
Okay, wait a minute. Wait a minute.
It's for you.

769
01:03:43,408 --> 01:03:45,200
Yes?

770
01:03:45,535 --> 01:03:47,113
How are you, dear?

771
01:03:47,788 --> 01:03:49,412
Oh, fine.

772
01:03:49,581 --> 01:03:53,081
No, honestly, much better.
In fact, all.

773
01:03:55,671 --> 01:03:57,129
What?

774
01:03:58,757 --> 01:04:00,251
Yeah.

775
01:04:04,096 --> 01:04:06,254
Well, to tell you the truth, Coll...

776
01:04:06,432 --> 01:04:11,177
...I'd just as soon you didn't,
such a long trip and all...

777
01:04:11,812 --> 01:04:15,228
...and you know how I get when you...

778
01:04:15,399 --> 01:04:18,435
Nothing, really.
He wants to come to the tournament.

779
01:04:18,611 --> 01:04:21,232
Tell him not to, will you?
He won't listen to me.

780
01:04:21,405 --> 01:04:23,279
Don't come.

781
01:04:24,158 --> 01:04:26,151
What? No. No, wait.

782
01:04:26,327 --> 01:04:29,826
You do understand, don't you, darling?

783
01:04:29,997 --> 01:04:33,082
Well, all right. No, no.
I'll write to you too.

784
01:04:33,584 --> 01:04:35,790
L... What?

785
01:04:39,048 --> 01:04:40,875
Now we gotta build
that left arm up...

786
01:04:41,050 --> 01:04:43,921
...otherwise your whole swing
goes cockeyed.

787
01:04:45,263 --> 01:04:46,805
Sit up.

788
01:04:49,475 --> 01:04:52,180
When you gonna get wise
to this Collier bash?

789
01:04:52,353 --> 01:04:54,310
Know what happened
when I was rubbing?

790
01:04:54,480 --> 01:04:57,232
You know what happened
to your muscles, huh?

791
01:04:57,400 --> 01:05:00,900
You got as tense as cold spaghetti.
I could feel it.

792
01:05:01,071 --> 01:05:03,609
- I'll get over it.
- Five'll get you 10 you don't.

793
01:05:03,782 --> 01:05:06,570
- Bet.
- Okay, I'll tell you what you do.

794
01:05:06,869 --> 01:05:10,285
Don't use the right at all, see?
Use the left until I tell differently.

795
01:05:10,456 --> 01:05:13,326
Don't use the right for nothing.
Not even to eat with, see?

796
01:05:13,501 --> 01:05:16,537
Everything with the left.
All right, lay down.

797
01:05:19,340 --> 01:05:21,083
Come on, push.

798
01:05:21,675 --> 01:05:23,170
Push.

799
01:05:26,639 --> 01:05:28,216
Push.

800
01:05:32,979 --> 01:05:35,185
- Now, to get back to this Collier thing.
- Yeah.

801
01:05:35,356 --> 01:05:38,108
- Yeah, I don't think so.
- In what way?

802
01:05:38,276 --> 01:05:40,814
- In no way.
- I mean, in what way not?

803
01:05:40,987 --> 01:05:44,190
- In no way not.
- How would you know?

804
01:05:44,365 --> 01:05:48,149
Oh, just by keeping my ears
and my eyes open and my so forth.

805
01:05:48,327 --> 01:05:52,325
I've been around. This man-woman thing,
that's gotta be a fifty-fifty thing.

806
01:05:52,498 --> 01:05:53,827
My feeling.

807
01:05:54,000 --> 01:05:57,286
He's 75.
You'll never be 5-0-5-0 with him.

808
01:05:57,670 --> 01:06:01,454
Why do you get yourself hooked
with a guy who's got his horns on you?

809
01:06:02,884 --> 01:06:04,544
That's all.

810
01:06:07,972 --> 01:06:10,298
- Let me ask you, Barney.
- Ask.

811
01:06:10,475 --> 01:06:13,227
- Why don't he examine me? Ain't l...?
- What?

812
01:06:13,395 --> 01:06:16,230
What's this? What are you doing?
You should be weighing in.

813
01:06:16,398 --> 01:06:18,723
- Tomorrow.
- What are you hanging around here for?

814
01:06:18,900 --> 01:06:22,150
- What's the matter with you?
- I don't wanna go in alone no more.

815
01:06:22,362 --> 01:06:23,690
Like lately.

816
01:06:23,863 --> 01:06:26,734
What do you want us to do?
All go with you? That'd be fine.

817
01:06:26,908 --> 01:06:28,984
The three of us could lick the guy,
but you're a big boy now.

818
01:06:29,161 --> 01:06:33,289
- You gotta learn to go in alone.
- I mean in the corner. You used to.

819
01:06:33,457 --> 01:06:36,209
- I'm busy.
- Yeah...

820
01:06:36,377 --> 01:06:39,331
- Busy.
- I gotta get ready to go south.

821
01:06:39,505 --> 01:06:42,257
What do you want me to do?
Tear myself into little pieces?

822
01:06:42,425 --> 01:06:43,884
Sure not.

823
01:06:44,052 --> 01:06:46,922
Trouble is, I haven't asked
the three big questions lately.

824
01:06:47,096 --> 01:06:50,845
- I don't wanna go in alone no more.
- Who made you, Hucko?

825
01:06:51,017 --> 01:06:53,686
What's the matter?
Can't you hear good? Who made you?

826
01:06:53,853 --> 01:06:56,724
- You, Mike.
- Who owns the biggest piece of you?

827
01:06:56,898 --> 01:06:59,436
- You, Mike.
- What'll happen if I drop you?

828
01:06:59,609 --> 01:07:02,017
- Go right down the drain.
- And?

829
01:07:02,195 --> 01:07:05,315
- And stay there.
- And don't ever forget it.

830
01:07:05,490 --> 01:07:09,274
Go back and tell Gibby if he lets you
loose again, he'll go down the drain too.

831
01:07:09,452 --> 01:07:12,702
- He'll go? I got it.
- Yeah.

832
01:07:13,373 --> 01:07:15,829
Now, what is with Little Nell?

833
01:07:18,628 --> 01:07:20,206
Hey.

834
01:07:22,007 --> 01:07:24,046
I don't like you.

835
01:07:24,217 --> 01:07:26,257
- I wish you did.
- But I don't.

836
01:07:26,428 --> 01:07:27,756
Why not?

837
01:07:27,929 --> 01:07:31,133
You made everything different
from what it used to in the old days.

838
01:07:31,308 --> 01:07:33,265
Last year.

839
01:07:33,435 --> 01:07:36,555
- How old are you, Hucko?
- A hundred ninety-seven and a half.

840
01:07:36,730 --> 01:07:38,272
- What?
- Pounds.

841
01:07:38,440 --> 01:07:40,100
No. How old?

842
01:07:40,275 --> 01:07:41,935
Twenty-four.

843
01:07:42,110 --> 01:07:44,233
Five. Three. Why?

844
01:07:44,404 --> 01:07:46,895
Anyhow, too old
for the three big questions.

845
01:07:47,074 --> 01:07:48,901
Hey, you want me to tell Mike on you?

846
01:07:49,076 --> 01:07:50,487
He didn't make you
and doesn't own you...

847
01:07:50,661 --> 01:07:52,534
...and you wouldn't go down
the drain if he dropped you.

848
01:07:52,704 --> 01:07:54,744
- And stay there.
- You wouldn't.

849
01:07:54,915 --> 01:07:57,240
Ought to belong to yourself.

850
01:07:58,043 --> 01:07:59,917
What do I want with myself?

851
01:08:00,087 --> 01:08:03,752
When you're in that ring, you shouldn't
worry about anyone, Mike or anyone.

852
01:08:03,924 --> 01:08:06,296
Yeah?
What about that guy I'm fighting?

853
01:08:06,468 --> 01:08:08,011
Not even him.

854
01:08:08,178 --> 01:08:10,468
You see, it's never you
against the whole world.

855
01:08:10,640 --> 01:08:13,262
Yeah, that's good.
I couldn't lick the whole world.

856
01:08:13,435 --> 01:08:16,851
- I don't think.
- Just you against yourself.

857
01:08:17,022 --> 01:08:18,397
Yeah?

858
01:08:18,565 --> 01:08:21,317
Well, I could lick myself, all right.

859
01:08:21,485 --> 01:08:24,023
- I think.
- You could?

860
01:08:24,196 --> 01:08:25,773
I think.

861
01:08:25,947 --> 01:08:28,818
That's all you have to do.
Lick yourself.

862
01:08:28,992 --> 01:08:30,901
Make yourself and own yourself.

863
01:08:31,078 --> 01:08:33,569
Never mind Mike or anyone.

864
01:08:33,747 --> 01:08:36,831
Hey, don't he never ask you
the three big questions?

865
01:08:37,000 --> 01:08:38,376
I wouldn't let him.

866
01:08:38,544 --> 01:08:41,165
See, I'm trying to lick myself too.

867
01:08:41,338 --> 01:08:43,627
Hey, the only thing...

868
01:08:43,799 --> 01:08:46,753
Why don't he examine me?

869
01:09:01,066 --> 01:09:02,726
So then:

870
01:09:04,069 --> 01:09:06,477
And then the bell:
End of the sixth.

871
01:09:06,655 --> 01:09:08,897
So then I breathe,
in and out, in and out.

872
01:09:09,074 --> 01:09:12,657
Oh, button it up, will you, Hucko?
We've been through this 40 times.

873
01:09:12,828 --> 01:09:16,032
- It's the seventh coming up. The end.
- Go ahead.

874
01:09:16,207 --> 01:09:18,495
I rush him. He's on his bike.

875
01:09:19,543 --> 01:09:22,213
He starts coming in.
That's when it happened, the thing.

876
01:09:22,380 --> 01:09:25,297
The big thing.
He's coming and I look.

877
01:09:25,466 --> 01:09:28,917
And who you think it is?
It's me. It's me coming at me.

878
01:09:29,095 --> 01:09:31,171
So I get mad.

879
01:09:34,142 --> 01:09:37,012
I'm hollering down his ear,
"Okay, Hucko."

880
01:09:37,186 --> 01:09:39,226
"Get this, Hucko."
Kidney punch.

881
01:09:39,397 --> 01:09:41,473
"You're through, Hucko."

882
01:09:43,484 --> 01:09:46,771
Now I go in. Before I throw it, even,
I knew already it was the one.

883
01:09:48,282 --> 01:09:50,773
And I seen him drop.

884
01:09:53,078 --> 01:09:56,946
And then after, when Gibby jumps in
and grabs me and gives me a kiss...

885
01:09:57,124 --> 01:10:00,576
...I says to him,
"You see me, how I flattened myself?"

886
01:10:01,170 --> 01:10:04,586
So he starts in putting cold towels
on my head.

887
01:10:05,091 --> 01:10:06,585
Okay. Take a walk.

888
01:10:06,759 --> 01:10:08,383
Okay, Mike.

889
01:10:08,552 --> 01:10:10,675
- Hey, can I lift her up?
- No.

890
01:10:10,846 --> 01:10:12,673
Just once?

891
01:10:12,848 --> 01:10:16,300
- All right, then blow.
- Yeah.

892
01:10:22,233 --> 01:10:24,356
Thanks, Mike.

893
01:10:27,780 --> 01:10:29,987
Could be he had his brains
knocked loose.

894
01:10:30,158 --> 01:10:31,901
Oh, he's fine.

895
01:10:32,076 --> 01:10:34,069
What's all this
fighting-yourself malarkey?

896
01:10:34,245 --> 01:10:36,570
How does a guy like that
pick up stuff like that?

897
01:10:36,748 --> 01:10:38,076
I wonder.

898
01:10:38,249 --> 01:10:39,874
Hey...

899
01:10:40,793 --> 01:10:43,284
- Me?
- What's doing here?

900
01:10:43,463 --> 01:10:45,705
You been talking at him?

901
01:10:46,466 --> 01:10:48,293
- Do you mind?
- No. No.

902
01:10:48,468 --> 01:10:52,051
I was gonna suggest maybe
you have a talk with Little Nell.

903
01:10:53,306 --> 01:10:55,464
- Mike?
- Now, we gotta go over schedules...

904
01:10:55,642 --> 01:10:57,101
- Yes, Mike.
- Yeah.

905
01:10:57,268 --> 01:11:00,934
This thing about getting the same room
as the last time I was down here.

906
01:11:01,106 --> 01:11:03,478
Is that just a coincidence,
or did you arrange it?

907
01:11:03,650 --> 01:11:05,643
Just a coincidence.

908
01:11:05,944 --> 01:11:07,771
Tell me the truth.

909
01:11:08,196 --> 01:11:09,571
I arranged it.

910
01:11:09,739 --> 01:11:12,028
- I thought so.
- Why?

911
01:11:12,200 --> 01:11:14,525
- Because I'm getting to know you.
- About time.

912
01:11:14,703 --> 01:11:17,454
And it turns out you're
just a big sentimental slob.

913
01:11:17,622 --> 01:11:19,580
Yeah, that's me.

914
01:11:19,833 --> 01:11:21,625
My, my, my.

915
01:11:21,794 --> 01:11:23,372
My, my, my, what?

916
01:11:23,546 --> 01:11:26,962
Oh, excuse me. I forgot to knock.

917
01:11:27,967 --> 01:11:29,627
Come in.

918
01:11:31,220 --> 01:11:32,928
- Guess who's here.
- Them.

919
01:11:33,097 --> 01:11:36,348
- How'd you know?
- Tell them to swing it in.

920
01:11:40,522 --> 01:11:41,850
- The boys.
- What boys?

921
01:11:42,023 --> 01:11:44,182
- The partners.
- I thought they were anonymous.

922
01:11:44,359 --> 01:11:47,146
Well, maybe they decided
to be non-anonymous.

923
01:11:47,320 --> 01:11:49,313
After all, these gentlemen
are no hoodlums.

924
01:11:49,489 --> 01:11:51,814
They're businessmen.
Plain, ordinary businessmen.

925
01:11:51,992 --> 01:11:54,529
- Investors.
- All the same.

926
01:11:54,703 --> 01:11:56,695
You can't have it perfect.

927
01:11:58,164 --> 01:11:59,872
Okay.

928
01:12:00,834 --> 01:12:02,162
- Hello, Spec.
- Hello, Mike.

929
01:12:02,335 --> 01:12:05,253
- Glad to see you. Hank, how are you?
- Could be worse.

930
01:12:05,422 --> 01:12:08,043
- Thought we'd like to see you, man.
- Well, you know me.

931
01:12:08,216 --> 01:12:10,292
Never too busy to say hello.

932
01:12:10,469 --> 01:12:13,339
- There she is.
- How do you do, gentlemen?

933
01:12:13,513 --> 01:12:15,589
- How do you do?
