Yeah, yeah, that's right.
Yeah, you got it down there all okay.

1163
01:24:29,517 --> 01:24:31,972
- Anything on him?
- Nothing.

1164
01:24:32,186 --> 01:24:35,851
All right, I wanna hold these two men
pending a report to Judge McEnroe...

1165
01:24:36,023 --> 01:24:39,392
...as to a violation of his order.
That's all. See you in the morning.

1166
01:24:39,569 --> 01:24:41,857
- Handle that, Kronski.
- Thanks.

1167
01:24:42,030 --> 01:24:44,402
Okay, we're adjourned.

1168
01:24:46,951 --> 01:24:48,743
How does it look
for tomorrow, anyway?

1169
01:24:48,911 --> 01:24:50,322
- Who knows?
- Well, good luck.

1170
01:24:50,496 --> 01:24:54,625
- I've got a few savings riding on you.
- Oh, thank you, goodbye.

1171
01:24:56,127 --> 01:24:57,835
Mike.

1172
01:24:58,004 --> 01:24:59,546
Mike!

1173
01:24:59,714 --> 01:25:02,750
- Mike, listen.
- I've been listening all night.

1174
01:25:02,926 --> 01:25:05,464
Then do you want to talk? I'll listen.

1175
01:25:06,012 --> 01:25:07,043
Leave me alone, will you?

1176
01:25:07,222 --> 01:25:10,555
I can understand your being upset,
but why with me? What have I done?

1177
01:25:10,725 --> 01:25:13,560
- Too much, that's what.
- But...

1178
01:25:14,688 --> 01:25:17,807
- Mike, don't be like this.
- Like what?

1179
01:25:17,983 --> 01:25:19,560
Lmpossible.

1180
01:25:19,734 --> 01:25:22,652
Oh, so that's what I am.
Impossible.

1181
01:25:23,029 --> 01:25:25,567
- Right now, yes.
- I don't happen to agree with you.

1182
01:25:25,740 --> 01:25:27,899
I think I'm possible.
I also think I'm stupid.

1183
01:25:28,076 --> 01:25:30,152
- Why?
- For the way I handle you, that's why.

1184
01:25:30,328 --> 01:25:33,614
I've built you up into some kind
of a Frankenstein monster.

1185
01:25:33,790 --> 01:25:37,455
That's what you are, you're just
a great big Mrs. Frankenstein.

1186
01:25:37,627 --> 01:25:41,496
You don't think this will get around?
You don't think everybody will know it?

1187
01:25:41,674 --> 01:25:45,126
I won't even be able
to show my face in Lindy's.

1188
01:25:45,303 --> 01:25:47,379
I don't like the combination.
I thought I would, but I don't.

1189
01:25:47,555 --> 01:25:49,097
I like everything to be 5-0-5-0.

1190
01:25:49,265 --> 01:25:52,136
I like a he to be a he
and a she to be a she.

1191
01:25:52,310 --> 01:25:53,970
But you said...

1192
01:25:58,233 --> 01:26:00,225
- Hold it.
- What?

1193
01:26:01,069 --> 01:26:02,397
- Go in the back way.
- Why?

1194
01:26:02,570 --> 01:26:05,655
- Quiet down.
- Why? Why?

1195
01:26:11,162 --> 01:26:13,736
- Oh, Pat!
- I think somebody's yelling "Pat."

1196
01:26:13,915 --> 01:26:15,575
No, cat. They're calling their cat.

1197
01:26:15,750 --> 01:26:17,743
- Pat, what's the matter?
- Hello, Collier.

1198
01:26:17,919 --> 01:26:19,995
Now, you come back
any time after the match.

1199
01:26:20,172 --> 01:26:21,880
- You're a little early now.
- Listen...

1200
01:26:22,048 --> 01:26:24,374
- Don't touch her right arm.
- Well, how about you?

1201
01:26:24,551 --> 01:26:27,505
- I got the other arm. Now, go away.
- Listen here, old man.

1202
01:26:27,679 --> 01:26:29,968
- Old man?
- I've got as much right as you have.

1203
01:26:30,140 --> 01:26:31,468
Come back in the morning...

1204
01:26:31,642 --> 01:26:34,761
Stop handling me, everybody, please!

1205
01:26:35,270 --> 01:26:39,138
You got a tough deal, all right,
there, buster. I feel for you.

1206
01:26:39,525 --> 01:26:41,398
Oh, you do?

1207
01:26:42,277 --> 01:26:44,768
That chick is sure stuck on you.

1208
01:26:44,947 --> 01:26:48,731
I can't quite understand why,
but there it is.

1209
01:26:49,701 --> 01:26:52,074
She's so stuck on you
that you jinx her.

1210
01:26:52,246 --> 01:26:55,366
You're in this business.
Have you ever heard of anything like it?

1211
01:26:55,541 --> 01:26:58,992
Oh, only two or three million times,
that's all.

1212
01:26:59,169 --> 01:27:02,005
You see, athletes,
they ain't like us, you know.

1213
01:27:02,172 --> 01:27:05,126
They're like what you call freaks.

1214
01:27:05,342 --> 01:27:07,631
Nobody can understand
how they do what they do.

1215
01:27:07,803 --> 01:27:11,848
They can't understand it themselves.
And different things throw them.

1216
01:27:12,016 --> 01:27:14,590
So who knows what,
why, where, when, see?

1217
01:27:14,770 --> 01:27:16,145
Yeah.

1218
01:27:16,605 --> 01:27:19,356
It's just like...
Now, you take little Joe Palone.

1219
01:27:19,524 --> 01:27:20,935
- Who?
- The jockey.

1220
01:27:21,109 --> 01:27:22,438
- Oh, yeah.
- Yeah.

1221
01:27:22,611 --> 01:27:25,778
For a long time my horse, Little Nell,
couldn't win nothing.

1222
01:27:25,948 --> 01:27:29,648
She couldn't win?
Say, she had trouble coming in last.

1223
01:27:29,826 --> 01:27:32,946
And I couldn't figure it.
And then I figured it.

1224
01:27:33,121 --> 01:27:35,695
She couldn't win
because Joe Palone was riding her.

1225
01:27:35,874 --> 01:27:38,579
I got rid. She won great.

1226
01:27:39,169 --> 01:27:41,791
It's the same in this case, buster.

1227
01:27:42,548 --> 01:27:45,418
You are the wrong jockey
for this chick.

1228
01:27:45,592 --> 01:27:48,878
- You don't say.
- Yeah, I do say.

1229
01:27:49,054 --> 01:27:51,676
So how about giving us all
a nice big break...

1230
01:27:51,849 --> 01:27:53,723
...and making yourself
scarce tomorrow?

1231
01:27:53,893 --> 01:27:55,684
- Why?
- Because, don't you understand?

1232
01:27:55,853 --> 01:27:58,095
When you're around,
she's no good. She's dead.

1233
01:27:58,272 --> 01:28:01,771
What you do after her working hours,
I don't care, go as far as you like.

1234
01:28:01,942 --> 01:28:04,101
But when she's on, you stay off.

1235
01:28:04,278 --> 01:28:05,606
- Can we deal?
- No.

1236
01:28:05,780 --> 01:28:08,401
- Why not?
- Your business doesn't interest me.

1237
01:28:08,574 --> 01:28:10,199
Tell me something, will you?

1238
01:28:10,368 --> 01:28:13,322
Were you born stubborn,
or did you learn this in college?

1239
01:28:13,496 --> 01:28:18,158
See you in the morning, Conovan.
On the first tee.

1240
01:29:55,016 --> 01:29:56,641
What?

1241
01:29:57,310 --> 01:29:59,766
Don't use your right arm.

1242
01:29:59,938 --> 01:30:02,559
- What is it?
- Go on. Be quiet. Go back to sleep.

1243
01:30:02,732 --> 01:30:04,690
How long have you been here?

1244
01:30:04,860 --> 01:30:06,852
I just came in
to check up, that's all.

1245
01:30:07,028 --> 01:30:09,270
The windows. I do it every night.

1246
01:30:09,447 --> 01:30:13,908
- You do what every night?
- Check the windows, fix the covers.

1247
01:30:14,578 --> 01:30:16,369
Sure.

1248
01:30:16,621 --> 01:30:18,947
Sometimes you kick them off.

1249
01:30:38,645 --> 01:30:40,887
What's the matter? You can't sleep?

1250
01:30:52,242 --> 01:30:54,567
Don't say anything.
Nothing, just shut up.

1251
01:30:54,744 --> 01:30:56,867
Why I didn't get on this
sooner than I have.

1252
01:30:57,038 --> 01:31:00,205
Always funny when it's happening
to some other guy, but not to me.

1253
01:31:00,375 --> 01:31:02,368
What makes you think
I'd stand in your way?

1254
01:31:02,544 --> 01:31:05,379
You want him? Go to it.
Looks to me you're perfectly suited.

1255
01:31:05,547 --> 01:31:06,958
- Two slick articles.
- Help!

1256
01:31:07,132 --> 01:31:09,006
Too nice to you,
that's my mistake.

1257
01:31:09,176 --> 01:31:12,130
- Too considerate.
- Mike!

1258
01:31:12,346 --> 01:31:14,054
- Mike!
- Be quiet.

1259
01:31:14,222 --> 01:31:16,096
Help!

1260
01:31:16,558 --> 01:31:17,887
- Help!
- Pipe down, will you?

1261
01:31:18,060 --> 01:31:20,811
You want everybody up here
and involve me in some kind...

1262
01:31:20,979 --> 01:31:24,395
- No. No. Mike, help.
- Quiet down, will you?

1263
01:31:24,566 --> 01:31:27,769
You're hurting me.
Collier, leave me alone.

1264
01:31:27,945 --> 01:31:29,653
Leave me alone.

1265
01:31:29,822 --> 01:31:31,150
What are you, some wild man?

1266
01:31:31,323 --> 01:31:35,237
No, just the wrong jockey.
But I guess you're the right one, all right.

1267
01:31:35,411 --> 01:31:37,534
- What's he talking...?
- Oh, come, come, now.

1268
01:31:37,705 --> 01:31:41,287
- Let's not give it the innocent.
- You don't think that...!

1269
01:31:41,458 --> 01:31:43,914
Tell him, will you? Talk!

1270
01:31:44,086 --> 01:31:46,079
What's the use?

1271
01:31:47,214 --> 01:31:50,049
No use, that's the use.
Well, congratulations.

1272
01:31:50,217 --> 01:31:53,467
But I wouldn't be surprised
if I'm not the lucky guy.

1273
01:31:56,724 --> 01:31:59,476
- What do you figure got into him?
- I don't know.

1274
01:31:59,643 --> 01:32:01,222
- He frightened me.
- I can imagine.

1275
01:32:01,396 --> 01:32:04,267
- Why I called you.
- Well, you done the right thing. Did.

1276
01:32:04,441 --> 01:32:07,727
I mean, what would I have did
if you hadn't been around?

1277
01:32:07,903 --> 01:32:10,192
- Done.
- I figure you can take care of yourself.

1278
01:32:10,364 --> 01:32:12,855
- No, I can't.
- Yeah, I bet you could even lick me...

1279
01:32:13,033 --> 01:32:14,693
- No, I couldn't.
- Sure, I think so.

1280
01:32:14,868 --> 01:32:17,193
No, I couldn't.
I need someone to look after me.

1281
01:32:17,371 --> 01:32:19,992
- Yeah? What about me?
- Why not?

1282
01:32:20,958 --> 01:32:22,749
I don't know if I can lick you...

1283
01:32:22,918 --> 01:32:25,207
...but I'll tell you one thing I do know.

1284
01:32:25,379 --> 01:32:27,170
- What?
- Together we can lick them all.

1285
01:32:27,339 --> 01:32:28,668
You bet.

1286
01:32:34,096 --> 01:32:36,634
I can't handle this in my head.
It rocks me.

1287
01:32:36,807 --> 01:32:39,096
- Why?
- Well, be as it don't figure.

1288
01:32:39,268 --> 01:32:42,601
It's like as though Hucko walked in
and handed me an engagement ring.

1289
01:32:42,771 --> 01:32:44,894
- I'm not Hucko.
- No, that you ain't.

1290
01:32:45,065 --> 01:32:47,272
- So?
- So I mean...

1291
01:32:47,443 --> 01:32:49,601
- There's one thing only about us.
- What?

1292
01:32:49,779 --> 01:32:52,566
Coming together,
that's what I call a plenty long shot.

1293
01:32:52,740 --> 01:32:55,824
- Nothing wrong with a long shot.
- Lf you come out on top.

1294
01:32:55,993 --> 01:32:57,404
We will, Mike.

1295
01:32:57,578 --> 01:33:00,247
As somehow, you don't seem to...

1296
01:33:00,414 --> 01:33:04,163
An upper-cruster like you
and my kind of type...

1297
01:33:04,335 --> 01:33:06,791
...that can't even speak
left-handed English yet.

1298
01:33:06,963 --> 01:33:09,917
- The whole jismo, it's hard to believe.
- It's not hard for me.

1299
01:33:10,133 --> 01:33:13,548
- I think so.
- I know so.

1300
01:33:16,180 --> 01:33:18,220
Okay, kid.

1301
01:33:18,391 --> 01:33:20,597
You got yourself a deal.

1302
01:33:31,696 --> 01:33:33,689
I'm gonna ask you
the three big questions.

1303
01:33:33,865 --> 01:33:35,489
- Go ahead.
- Who made you?

1304
01:33:35,658 --> 01:33:36,691
You did.

1305
01:33:47,755 --> 01:33:49,831
- Who owns the biggest piece of you?
- You do.

1306
01:34:20,663 --> 01:34:23,830
- What would happen if I dropped you?
- I'd go right down the drain.

1307
01:34:24,000 --> 01:34:26,538
- And?
- Take you right down with me, shorty.

